# Accessibility Rules

## Platform Requirements

- Support `AccessibilityRequirement` enum on all booking flows.
- WCAG 2.1 AA minimum for customer and operator web apps.

## Web

- Semantic HTML: `main`, `nav`, `section`, heading hierarchy.
- Focus visible on all interactive elements.
- Skip link to main content on dashboard layouts.
- Form errors linked via `aria-describedby`.

## Booking

- Offer step-free / wheelchair options without burying in advanced settings.
- Phone booking parity: operator can enter accessibility needs on behalf of customer.

## Testing

- axe-core in CI for web critical paths.
- Manual test with VoiceOver (iOS) and TalkBack (Android) before release.
